{"word":"προσπολέω","slug":"προσπολέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>προσπολέω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ήσω</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:πρόσπολος'><el>πρόσπολος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to attend, serve</i>, <el>τινί</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be escorted by a train of attendants</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}